Soft and fluffy on the inside but perfectly golden and crisp on the outside French toast sticks are perfect for breakfast with friends and family. Ingredients Instructions Step 1: Heat about oil in a large heavy pan on low heat. Step 2: Combine milk, flour, eggs, sugar, baking powder, vanilla and salt in a bowl. Cut the bread slices into sticks. Step 3: In another dish, combine the sugar and cinnamon for the coating. Step 4: When the oil is hot, dip a slice of the bread in the paste in Step 2, turning quickly to coat. Don’t soak for too long. Repeat with the rest of the remaining bread. Step 5: Coat the bread with cinnamon and sugar as desired and serve with your favorite syrup.